40// Max in the RFC 3550 is 255 bytes, we limit it to be modulus 32 for SRTP.
41constexpr size_t kMaxPaddingLength = 224;
42constexpr size_t kMinAudioPaddingLength = 50;
43constexpr size_t kRtpHeaderLength = 12;
44constexpr uint16_t kMaxInitRtpSeqNumber = 32767; // 2^15 -1.
45
46// Min size needed to get payload padding from packet history.
47constexpr int kMinPayloadPaddingBytes = 50;
48
49template <typename Extension>
50constexpr RtpExtensionSize CreateExtensionSize() {
51 return {Extension::kId, Extension::kValueSizeBytes};
52}
53
54template <typename Extension>
55constexpr RtpExtensionSize CreateMaxExtensionSize() {
56 return {Extension::kId, Extension::kMaxValueSizeBytes};
57}
58
59// Size info for header extensions that might be used in padding or FEC packets.
60constexpr RtpExtensionSize kFecOrPaddingExtensionSizes[] = {
61 CreateExtensionSize<AbsoluteSendTime>(),
62 CreateExtensionSize<TransmissionOffset>(),
63 CreateExtensionSize<TransportSequenceNumber>(),
64 CreateExtensionSize<PlayoutDelayLimits>(),
65 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RtpMid>(),
66 CreateExtensionSize<VideoTimingExtension>(),
67};
68
69// Size info for header extensions that might be used in video packets.
70constexpr RtpExtensionSize kVideoExtensionSizes[] = {
71 CreateExtensionSize<AbsoluteSendTime>(),
72 CreateExtensionSize<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(),
73 CreateExtensionSize<TransmissionOffset>(),
74 CreateExtensionSize<TransportSequenceNumber>(),
75 CreateExtensionSize<PlayoutDelayLimits>(),
76 CreateExtensionSize<VideoOrientation>(),
77 CreateExtensionSize<VideoContentTypeExtension>(),
78 CreateExtensionSize<VideoTimingExtension>(),
79 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RtpStreamId>(),
80 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RepairedRtpStreamId>(),
81 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RtpMid>(),
82 {RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00::kId,
83 RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00::kMaxSizeBytes},
84};
85
86// Size info for header extensions that might be used in audio packets.
87constexpr RtpExtensionSize kAudioExtensionSizes[] = {
88 CreateExtensionSize<AbsoluteSendTime>(),
89 CreateExtensionSize<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(),
90 CreateExtensionSize<AudioLevel>(),
91 CreateExtensionSize<InbandComfortNoiseExtension>(),
92 CreateExtensionSize<TransmissionOffset>(),
93 CreateExtensionSize<TransportSequenceNumber>(),
94 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RtpStreamId>(),
95 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RepairedRtpStreamId>(),
96 CreateMaxExtensionSize<RtpMid>(),
97};
98
99// Non-volatile extensions can be expected on all packets, if registered.
100// Volatile ones, such as VideoContentTypeExtension which is only set on
101// key-frames, are removed to simplify overhead calculations at the expense of
102// some accuracy.
103bool IsNonVolatile(RTPExtensionType type) {
104 switch (type) {
105 case kRtpExtensionTransmissionTimeOffset:
106 case kRtpExtensionAudioLevel:
107 case kRtpExtensionAbsoluteSendTime:
108 case kRtpExtensionTransportSequenceNumber:
109 case kRtpExtensionTransportSequenceNumber02:
110 case kRtpExtensionRtpStreamId:
111 case kRtpExtensionMid:
112 case kRtpExtensionGenericFrameDescriptor00:
113 case kRtpExtensionGenericFrameDescriptor02:
114 return true;
115 case kRtpExtensionInbandComfortNoise:
116 case kRtpExtensionAbsoluteCaptureTime:
117 case kRtpExtensionVideoRotation:
118 case kRtpExtensionPlayoutDelay:
119 case kRtpExtensionVideoContentType:
120 case kRtpExtensionVideoLayersAllocation:
121 case kRtpExtensionVideoTiming:
122 case kRtpExtensionRepairedRtpStreamId:
123 case kRtpExtensionColorSpace:
124 case kRtpExtensionVideoFrameTrackingId:
125 return false;
126 case kRtpExtensionNone:
127 case kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions:
128 RTC_NOTREACHED();
129 return false;
130 }
131 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
132}
133
134bool HasBweExtension(const RtpHeaderExtensionMap& extensions_map) {
135 return extensions_map.IsRegistered(kRtpExtensionTransportSequenceNumber) ||
136 extensions_map.IsRegistered(kRtpExtensionTransportSequenceNumber02) ||
137 extensions_map.IsRegistered(kRtpExtensionAbsoluteSendTime) ||
138 extensions_map.IsRegistered(kRtpExtensionTransmissionTimeOffset);
139}
140
141double GetMaxPaddingSizeFactor(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials) {
142 // Too low factor means RTX payload padding is rarely used and ineffective.
143 // Too high means we risk interrupting regular media packets.
144 // In practice, 3x seems to yield reasonable results.
145 constexpr double kDefaultFactor = 3.0;
146 if (!field_trials) {
147 return kDefaultFactor;
148 }
149
150 FieldTrialOptional<double> factor("factor", kDefaultFactor);
151 ParseFieldTrial({&factor}, field_trials->Lookup("WebRTC-LimitPaddingSize"));
152 RTC_CHECK_GE(factor.Value(), 0.0);
153 return factor.Value();
154}

158RTPSender::RTPSender(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
159 RtpPacketHistory* packet_history,
160 RtpPacketSender* packet_sender)
161 : clock_(config.clock),
162 random_(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()),
163 audio_configured_(config.audio),
164 ssrc_(config.local_media_ssrc),
165 rtx_ssrc_(config.rtx_send_ssrc),
166 flexfec_ssrc_(config.fec_generator ? config.fec_generator->FecSsrc()
167 : absl::nullopt),
168 max_padding_size_factor_(GetMaxPaddingSizeFactor(config.field_trials)),
169 packet_history_(packet_history),
170 paced_sender_(packet_sender),
171 sending_media_(true), // Default to sending media.
172 max_packet_size_(IP_PACKET_SIZE - 28), // Default is IP-v4/UDP.
173 rtp_header_extension_map_(config.extmap_allow_mixed),
174 // RTP variables
175 sequencer_(config.local_media_ssrc,
176 config.rtx_send_ssrc.value_or(config.local_media_ssrc),
177 /*require_marker_before_media_padding_=*/!config.audio,
178 config.clock),
179 always_send_mid_and_rid_(config.always_send_mid_and_rid),
180 ssrc_has_acked_(false),
181 rtx_ssrc_has_acked_(false),
182 csrcs_(),
183 rtx_(kRtxOff),
184 supports_bwe_extension_(false),
185 retransmission_rate_limiter_(config.retransmission_rate_limiter) {
186 UpdateHeaderSizes();
187 // This random initialization is not intended to be cryptographic strong.
188 timestamp_offset_ = random_.Rand<uint32_t>();
189 // Random start, 16 bits. Can't be 0.
190 sequencer_.set_rtx_sequence_number(random_.Rand(1, kMaxInitRtpSeqNumber));
191 sequencer_.set_media_sequence_number(random_.Rand(1, kMaxInitRtpSeqNumber));
192
193 RTC_DCHECK(paced_sender_);
194 RTC_DCHECK(packet_history_);
195}

278void RTPSender::SetRtxPayloadType(int payload_type,
279 int associated_payload_type) {
280 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
281 RTC_DCHECK_LE(payload_type, 127);
282 RTC_DCHECK_LE(associated_payload_type, 127);
283 if (payload_type < 0) {
284 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Invalid RTX payload type: " << payload_type << ".";
285 return;
286 }
287
288 rtx_payload_type_map_[associated_payload_type] = payload_type;
289}

291int32_t RTPSender::ReSendPacket(uint16_t packet_id) {
292 // Try to find packet in RTP packet history. Also verify RTT here, so that we
293 // don't retransmit too often.
294 absl::optional<RtpPacketHistory::PacketState> stored_packet =
295 packet_history_->GetPacketState(packet_id);
296 if (!stored_packet || stored_packet->pending_transmission) {
297 // Packet not found or already queued for retransmission, ignore.
298 return 0;
299 }
300
301 const int32_t packet_size = static_cast<int32_t>(stored_packet->packet_size);
302 const bool rtx = (RtxStatus() & kRtxRetransmitted) > 0;
303
304 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet =
305 packet_history_->GetPacketAndMarkAsPending(
306 packet_id, [&](const RtpPacketToSend& stored_packet) {
307 // Check if we're overusing retransmission bitrate.
308 // TODO(sprang): Add histograms for nack success or failure
309 // reasons.
310 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> retransmit_packet;
311 if (retransmission_rate_limiter_ &&
312 !retransmission_rate_limiter_->TryUseRate(packet_size)) {
313 return retransmit_packet;
314 }
315 if (rtx) {
316 retransmit_packet = BuildRtxPacket(stored_packet);
317 } else {
318 retransmit_packet =
319 std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(stored_packet);
320 }
321 if (retransmit_packet) {
322 retransmit_packet->set_retransmitted_sequence_number(
323 stored_packet.SequenceNumber());
324 }
325 return retransmit_packet;
326 });
327 if (!packet) {
328 return -1;
329 }
330 packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission);
331 packet->set_fec_protect_packet(false);
332 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets;
333 packets.emplace_back(std::move(packet));
334 paced_sender_->EnqueuePackets(std::move(packets));
335
336 return packet_size;
337}

357
358void RTPSender::OnReceivedNack(
359 const std::vector<uint16_t>& nack_sequence_numbers,
360 int64_t avg_rtt) {
361 packet_history_->SetRtt(5 + avg_rtt);
362 for (uint16_t seq_no : nack_sequence_numbers) {
363 const int32_t bytes_sent = ReSendPacket(seq_no);
364 if (bytes_sent < 0) {
365 // Failed to send one Sequence number. Give up the rest in this nack.
366 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed resending RTP packet " << seq_no
367 << ", Discard rest of packets.";
368 break;
369 }
370 }
371}

384std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> RTPSender::GeneratePadding(
385 size_t target_size_bytes,
386 bool media_has_been_sent) {
387 // This method does not actually send packets, it just generates
388 // them and puts them in the pacer queue. Since this should incur
389 // low overhead, keep the lock for the scope of the method in order
390 // to make the code more readable.
391
392 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> padding_packets;
393 size_t bytes_left = target_size_bytes;
394 if (SupportsRtxPayloadPadding()) {
395 while (bytes_left >= kMinPayloadPaddingBytes) {
396 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet =
397 packet_history_->GetPayloadPaddingPacket(
398 [&](const RtpPacketToSend& packet)
399 -> std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> {
400 // Limit overshoot, generate <= |max_padding_size_factor_| *
401 // target_size_bytes.
402 const size_t max_overshoot_bytes = static_cast<size_t>(
403 ((max_padding_size_factor_ - 1.0) * target_size_bytes) +
404 0.5);
405 if (packet.payload_size() + kRtxHeaderSize >
406 max_overshoot_bytes + bytes_left) {
407 return nullptr;
408 }
409 return BuildRtxPacket(packet);
410 });
411 if (!packet) {
412 break;
413 }
414
415 bytes_left -= std::min(bytes_left, packet->payload_size());
416 packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding);
417 padding_packets.push_back(std::move(packet));
418 }
419 }
420
421 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
422 if (!sending_media_) {
423 return {};
424 }
425
426 size_t padding_bytes_in_packet;
427 const size_t max_payload_size =
428 max_packet_size_ - max_padding_fec_packet_header_;
429 if (audio_configured_) {
430 // Allow smaller padding packets for audio.
431 padding_bytes_in_packet = rtc::SafeClamp<size_t>(
432 bytes_left, kMinAudioPaddingLength,
433 rtc::SafeMin(max_payload_size, kMaxPaddingLength));
434 } else {
435 // Always send full padding packets. This is accounted for by the
436 // RtpPacketSender, which will make sure we don't send too much padding even
437 // if a single packet is larger than requested.
438 // We do this to avoid frequently sending small packets on higher bitrates.
439 padding_bytes_in_packet = rtc::SafeMin(max_payload_size, kMaxPaddingLength);
440 }
441
442 while (bytes_left > 0) {
443 auto padding_packet =
444 std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(&rtp_header_extension_map_);
445 padding_packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding);
446 padding_packet->SetMarker(false);
447 if (rtx_ == kRtxOff) {
448 padding_packet->SetSsrc(ssrc_);
449 if (!sequencer_.Sequence(*padding_packet)) {
450 break;
451 }
452 } else {
453 // Without abs-send-time or transport sequence number a media packet
454 // must be sent before padding so that the timestamps used for
455 // estimation are correct.
456 if (!media_has_been_sent &&
457 !(rtp_header_extension_map_.IsRegistered(AbsoluteSendTime::kId) ||
458 rtp_header_extension_map_.IsRegistered(
459 TransportSequenceNumber::kId))) {
460 break;
461 }
462
463 RTC_DCHECK(rtx_ssrc_);
464 padding_packet->SetSsrc(*rtx_ssrc_);
465 padding_packet->SetPayloadType(rtx_payload_type_map_.begin()->second);
466 if (!sequencer_.Sequence(*padding_packet)) {
467 break;
468 }
469 }
470
471 if (rtp_header_extension_map_.IsRegistered(TransportSequenceNumber::kId)) {
472 padding_packet->ReserveExtension<TransportSequenceNumber>();
473 }
474 if (rtp_header_extension_map_.IsRegistered(TransmissionOffset::kId)) {
475 padding_packet->ReserveExtension<TransmissionOffset>();
476 }
477 if (rtp_header_extension_map_.IsRegistered(AbsoluteSendTime::kId)) {
478 padding_packet->ReserveExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>();
479 }
480
481 padding_packet->SetPadding(padding_bytes_in_packet);
482 bytes_left -= std::min(bytes_left, padding_bytes_in_packet);
483 padding_packets.push_back(std::move(padding_packet));
484 }
485
486 return padding_packets;
487}
488
489bool RTPSender::SendToNetwork(std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet) {
490 RTC_DCHECK(packet);
491 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
492
493 auto packet_type = packet->packet_type();
494 RTC_CHECK(packet_type) << "Packet type must be set before sending.";
495
496 if (packet->capture_time_ms() <= 0) {
497 packet->set_capture_time_ms(now_ms);
498 }
499
500 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets;
501 packets.emplace_back(std::move(packet));
502 paced_sender_->EnqueuePackets(std::move(packets));
503
504 return true;
505}
506
507void RTPSender::EnqueuePackets(
508 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets) {
509 RTC_DCHECK(!packets.empty());
510 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
511 for (auto& packet : packets) {
512 RTC_DCHECK(packet);
513 RTC_CHECK(packet->packet_type().has_value())
514 << "Packet type must be set before sending.";
515 if (packet->capture_time_ms() <= 0) {
516 packet->set_capture_time_ms(now_ms);
517 }
518 }
519
520 paced_sender_->EnqueuePackets(std::move(packets));
521}

533std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> RTPSender::AllocatePacket() const {
534 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
535 // TODO(danilchap): Find better motivator and value for extra capacity.
536 // RtpPacketizer might slightly miscalulate needed size,
537 // SRTP may benefit from extra space in the buffer and do encryption in place
538 // saving reallocation.
539 // While sending slightly oversized packet increase chance of dropped packet,
540 // it is better than crash on drop packet without trying to send it.
541 static constexpr int kExtraCapacity = 16;
542 auto packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(
543 &rtp_header_extension_map_, max_packet_size_ + kExtraCapacity);
544 packet->SetSsrc(ssrc_);
545 packet->SetCsrcs(csrcs_);
546 // Reserve extensions, if registered, RtpSender set in SendToNetwork.
547 packet->ReserveExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>();
548 packet->ReserveExtension<TransmissionOffset>();
549 packet->ReserveExtension<TransportSequenceNumber>();
550
551 // BUNDLE requires that the receiver "bind" the received SSRC to the values
552 // in the MID and/or (R)RID header extensions if present. Therefore, the
553 // sender can reduce overhead by omitting these header extensions once it
554 // knows that the receiver has "bound" the SSRC.
555 // This optimization can be configured by setting
556 // |always_send_mid_and_rid_| appropriately.
557 //
558 // The algorithm here is fairly simple: Always attach a MID and/or RID (if
559 // configured) to the outgoing packets until an RTCP receiver report comes
560 // back for this SSRC. That feedback indicates the receiver must have
561 // received a packet with the SSRC and header extension(s), so the sender
562 // then stops attaching the MID and RID.
563 if (always_send_mid_and_rid_ || !ssrc_has_acked_) {
564 // These are no-ops if the corresponding header extension is not registered.
565 if (!mid_.empty()) {
566 packet->SetExtension<RtpMid>(mid_);
567 }
568 if (!rid_.empty()) {
569 packet->SetExtension<RtpStreamId>(rid_);
570 }
571 }
572 return packet;
573}

640
641void RTPSender::SetSequenceNumber(uint16_t seq) {
642 bool updated_sequence_number = false;
643 {
644 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
645 if (sequencer_.media_sequence_number() != seq) {
646 updated_sequence_number = true;
647 }
648 sequencer_.set_media_sequence_number(seq);
649 }
650
651 if (updated_sequence_number) {
652 // Sequence number series has been reset to a new value, clear RTP packet
653 // history, since any packets there may conflict with new ones.
654 packet_history_->Clear();
655 }
656}
657
658uint16_t RTPSender::SequenceNumber() const {
659 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
660 return sequencer_.media_sequence_number();
661}
662
663static void CopyHeaderAndExtensionsToRtxPacket(const RtpPacketToSend& packet,
664 RtpPacketToSend* rtx_packet) {
665 // Set the relevant fixed packet headers. The following are not set:
666 // * Payload type - it is replaced in rtx packets.
667 // * Sequence number - RTX has a separate sequence numbering.
668 // * SSRC - RTX stream has its own SSRC.
669 rtx_packet->SetMarker(packet.Marker());
670 rtx_packet->SetTimestamp(packet.Timestamp());
671
672 // Set the variable fields in the packet header:
673 // * CSRCs - must be set before header extensions.
674 // * Header extensions - replace Rid header with RepairedRid header.
675 const std::vector<uint32_t> csrcs = packet.Csrcs();
676 rtx_packet->SetCsrcs(csrcs);
677 for (int extension_num = kRtpExtensionNone + 1;
678 extension_num < kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions; ++extension_num) {
679 auto extension = static_cast<RTPExtensionType>(extension_num);
680
681 // Stream ID header extensions (MID, RSID) are sent per-SSRC. Since RTX
682 // operates on a different SSRC, the presence and values of these header
683 // extensions should be determined separately and not blindly copied.
684 if (extension == kRtpExtensionMid ||
685 extension == kRtpExtensionRtpStreamId) {
686 continue;
687 }
688
689 // Empty extensions should be supported, so not checking |source.empty()|.
690 if (!packet.HasExtension(extension)) {
691 continue;
692 }
693
694 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> source = packet.FindExtension(extension);
695
696 rtc::ArrayView<uint8_t> destination =
697 rtx_packet->AllocateExtension(extension, source.size());
698
699 // Could happen if any:
700 // 1. Extension has 0 length.
701 // 2. Extension is not registered in destination.
702 // 3. Allocating extension in destination failed.
703 if (destination.empty() || source.size() != destination.size()) {
704 continue;
705 }
706
707 std::memcpy(destination.begin(), source.begin(), destination.size());
708 }
709}
710
711std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> RTPSender::BuildRtxPacket(
712 const RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
713 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> rtx_packet;
714
715 // Add original RTP header.
716 {
717 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
718 if (!sending_media_)
719 return nullptr;
720
721 RTC_DCHECK(rtx_ssrc_);
722
723 // Replace payload type.
724 auto kv = rtx_payload_type_map_.find(packet.PayloadType());
725 if (kv == rtx_payload_type_map_.end())
726 return nullptr;
727
728 rtx_packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(&rtp_header_extension_map_,
729 max_packet_size_);
730
731 rtx_packet->SetPayloadType(kv->second);
732
733 // Replace SSRC.
734 rtx_packet->SetSsrc(*rtx_ssrc_);
735
736 // Replace sequence number.
737 sequencer_.Sequence(*rtx_packet);
738
739 CopyHeaderAndExtensionsToRtxPacket(packet, rtx_packet.get());
740
741 // RTX packets are sent on an SSRC different from the main media, so the
742 // decision to attach MID and/or RRID header extensions is completely
743 // separate from that of the main media SSRC.
744 //
745 // Note that RTX packets must used the RepairedRtpStreamId (RRID) header
746 // extension instead of the RtpStreamId (RID) header extension even though
747 // the payload is identical.
748 if (always_send_mid_and_rid_ || !rtx_ssrc_has_acked_) {
749 // These are no-ops if the corresponding header extension is not
750 // registered.
751 if (!mid_.empty()) {
752 rtx_packet->SetExtension<RtpMid>(mid_);
753 }
754 if (!rid_.empty()) {
755 rtx_packet->SetExtension<RepairedRtpStreamId>(rid_);
756 }
757 }
758 }
759 RTC_DCHECK(rtx_packet);
760
761 uint8_t* rtx_payload =
762 rtx_packet->AllocatePayload(packet.payload_size() + kRtxHeaderSize);
763 if (rtx_payload == nullptr)
764 return nullptr;
765
766 // Add OSN (original sequence number).
767 ByteWriter<uint16_t>::WriteBigEndian(rtx_payload, packet.SequenceNumber());
768
769 // Add original payload data.
770 auto payload = packet.payload();
771 memcpy(rtx_payload + kRtxHeaderSize, payload.data(), payload.size());
772
773 // Add original additional data.
774 rtx_packet->set_additional_data(packet.additional_data());
775
776 // Copy capture time so e.g. TransmissionOffset is correctly set.
777 rtx_packet->set_capture_time_ms(packet.capture_time_ms());
778
779 return rtx_packet;
780}

782void RTPSender::SetRtpState(const RtpState& rtp_state) {
783 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
784
785 timestamp_offset_ = rtp_state.start_timestamp;
786 sequencer_.SetRtpState(rtp_state);
787 ssrc_has_acked_ = rtp_state.ssrc_has_acked;
788 UpdateHeaderSizes();
789}
790
791RtpState RTPSender::GetRtpState() const {
792 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
793
794 RtpState state;
795 state.start_timestamp = timestamp_offset_;
796 state.ssrc_has_acked = ssrc_has_acked_;
797 sequencer_.PupulateRtpState(state);
798 return state;
799}

801void RTPSender::SetRtxRtpState(const RtpState& rtp_state) {
802 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
803 sequencer_.set_rtx_sequence_number(rtp_state.sequence_number);
804 rtx_ssrc_has_acked_ = rtp_state.ssrc_has_acked;
805}

807RtpState RTPSender::GetRtxRtpState() const {
808 MutexLock lock(&send_mutex_);
809
810 RtpState state;
811 state.sequence_number = sequencer_.rtx_sequence_number();
812 state.start_timestamp = timestamp_offset_;
813 state.ssrc_has_acked = rtx_ssrc_has_acked_;
814
815 return state;
816}
817
818void RTPSender::UpdateHeaderSizes() {
819 const size_t rtp_header_length =
820 kRtpHeaderLength + sizeof(uint32_t) * csrcs_.size();
821
822 max_padding_fec_packet_header_ =
823 rtp_header_length + RtpHeaderExtensionSize(kFecOrPaddingExtensionSizes,
824 rtp_header_extension_map_);
825
826 // RtpStreamId and Mid are treated specially in that we check if they
827 // currently are being sent. RepairedRtpStreamId is ignored because it is sent
828 // instead of RtpStreamId on rtx packets and require the same size.
829 const bool send_mid_rid_on_rtx =
830 rtx_ssrc_.has_value() && !rtx_ssrc_has_acked_;
831 const bool send_mid_rid =
832 always_send_mid_and_rid_ || !ssrc_has_acked_ || send_mid_rid_on_rtx;
833 std::vector<RtpExtensionSize> non_volatile_extensions;
834 for (auto& extension :
835 audio_configured_ ? AudioExtensionSizes() : VideoExtensionSizes()) {
836 if (IsNonVolatile(extension.type)) {
837 switch (extension.type) {
838 case RTPExtensionType::kRtpExtensionMid:
839 if (send_mid_rid && !mid_.empty()) {
840 non_volatile_extensions.push_back(extension);
841 }
842 break;
843 case RTPExtensionType::kRtpExtensionRtpStreamId:
844 if (send_mid_rid && !rid_.empty()) {
845 non_volatile_extensions.push_back(extension);
846 }
847 break;
848 default:
849 non_volatile_extensions.push_back(extension);
850 }
851 }
852 }
853 max_media_packet_header_ =
854 rtp_header_length + RtpHeaderExtensionSize(non_volatile_extensions,
855 rtp_header_extension_map_);
856 // Reserve extra bytes if packet might be resent in an rtx packet.
857 if (rtx_ssrc_.has_value()) {
858 max_media_packet_header_ += kRtxHeaderSize;
859 }
860}
